channel.title: Moparscape randomly closes sometime before cache finishes downloading
channel.description: I haven't been able to play the game yet because of what I described in the title. My first few tries were on the online version at moparisthebest.com, in which case all of my browser windows would suddenly close, but now I'm trying with the jar version and that's the only thing that closes. I've tried at least ten times now. Why is this happening, and why doesn't the download pick up where it leaves off?

item.title: Moparscape randomly closes sometime before cache finishes downloading
item.dc:creator: @Cab Cab
item.description:
@Cab wrote:

I downloaded the cache, but now winrar is giving me this BS…

Upon opening the archive…
! C:\Documents and Settings\Owner\Desktop\cache.zip: Unexpected end of archive

Upon trying to extract to C:\WINDOWS.mpr_file_store_32…
! C:\Documents and Settings\Owner\Desktop\cache.zip: The archive is either in unknown format or damaged

Any idea what’s up? I tried deleting and redownloading it, but same thing. Also, I don’t know if this means anything, but the download was acting a bit stange. What I mean by that is that it was downloading at around 200mbps according to the computer (and the estimated-finish timer was lined up as such), but only about 100kb’s got added to the download every five seconds instead of a megabyte. Weird.
